{{!-- After the End — slides.
     Inherits {{title}}, {{{content}}}, {{feature_image}} from the parent
     post.hbs's #post block. Press quote and media slide URLs
     are hardcoded here. Image URLs hotlink to the production Ghost CDN —
     swap to local theme assets later if you want to fully self-host. --}}

{{!-- ── INTRO SLIDE ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── --}}
<article class="archive-entry archive-entry--intro is-active" data-index="0">

  <div class="archive-entry-image">
    {{#if feature_image}}
      <img
        src="{{img_url feature_image size="xl"}}"
        alt="{{title}}"
        loading="eager"
      />
    {{else}}
      <img
        src="https://jamesreeves.ghost.io/content/images/2024/05/walter-wlodarczyk-2021-11-03-_89A0465-1500x1001@2x.jpg"
        alt="{{title}}"
        loading="eager"
      />
    {{/if}}
    {{> "feature-image-caption"}}
  </div>

  <div class="archive-entry-content">
    <blockquote class="archive-press-quote">
      &ldquo;Memorial artworks are notoriously difficult to pull off. Yet Candy Chang and James A. Reeves, two New York artists who have created similar installations in the past, hit just the right tone with After the End, a participatory work in the Historic Chapel at Green-Wood Cemetery.&rdquo;
    </blockquote>
    <p class="archive-press-source">The New York Times</p>

    <div class="archive-entry-text">
      <h1 class="archive-entry-title">{{title}}</h1>
      <div class="archive-entry-body">
        {{{content}}}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</article>


{{!-- ── MEDIA SLIDES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
     Local assets under /assets/public-works/after-the-end/. Add more
     after-N.webp files there and a matching <article> block here (with
     data-index incremented) to grow the deck. data-caption is per-slide
     so future slides can attribute different photographers if needed.

     NOTE: We use hardcoded /assets/... paths instead of {{asset}} here
     because Ghost's asset helper conflicts with the /public-works/
     collection permalink defined in routes.yaml — the helper strips the
     /assets/ prefix when the rest of the path matches a routed URL
     pattern. Trade-off: no automatic cache-busting query param. Fine
     for these — they change once every couple years. If you ever need
     to bust the browser cache, append ?v=YYYY-MM-DD manually. --}}

<article class="archive-entry archive-entry--media" data-index="1" data-caption="Photo by Walter Wlodarczyk">
  <div class="archive-entry-image archive-entry-image--full">
    <img loading="lazy" alt="" src="/assets/public-works/after-the-end/after-1.webp" />
  </div>
</article>

